#Tutor Instructions
Hand out the tutorial to all students. Individual students should complete the sections 1 to 4 (20 minutes)
Marking. Divide the class into groups of five and give each group, five of the completed tutorial sheets from the other students, such that the group is not marking their own work. Each group should discuss and complete the marking section for each tutorial sheet (30 minutes).
Presentation. A member from each group must verbally present to the class; which of the five initial project ideas is the best and why, and how that idea could be improved, which of the five Initial project ideas is the worst and why, and how that idea could be improved.
Return the tutorial sheets to the students. Students must upload the completed tutorial sheet into Moodle. Tutorial Upload - Initial Idea
At the end of the tutorial, inform students, they must complete and present the following documents for next week's tutorial.
•	Five Journal papers, written up using the Journal Template
•	How to Select a Project Topic
•	Week Planner
 
